Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.00,1:03:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,hills. The fire had died to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.50,1:03:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,embers. The morning light came
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.24,1:03:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,through the cracks in the window
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.10,1:03:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in grey bands. I land a slept
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.79,1:03:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.02,1:03:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,her hand over mine. My hand
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.48,1:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,still on her belly. I stayed
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.00,1:03:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at her face for a time I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.73,1:03:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't measure.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.54,1:03:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a decision I'd put off
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.22,1:03:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for three months that would stop
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.90,1:03:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,being postponable the moment she
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.58,1:03:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,opened her eyes. I'd written
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.15,1:03:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that clause alone in my father's
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.94,1:03:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,study, a week before sitting at
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.67,1:03:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.84,1:03:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,cafe Vecca Roma across from her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.47,1:03:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote it because I didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.85,1:03:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,believe a woman could stay with
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.43,1:03:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,me for
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.74,1:03:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,anything other than fear or
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.24,1:03:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,debt. I wrote it because I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.68,1:03:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to leave an exit door
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.24,1:03:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,open for her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.98,1:03:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote it because the only love
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.55,1:03:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd learned to give was
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.68,1:03:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to leave. I spent
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.05,1:03:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,three
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.30,1:03:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,whole months knowing that she'd
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.09,1:03:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,still existed. I put off
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.47,1:03:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,destroying it. I thought I'd
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.08,1:03:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,have time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.06,1:03:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought erasing it later would
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.81,1:03:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,count the same as never having
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.44,1:03:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,written it. It didn't. As long
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.08,1:03:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as that clause was in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.89,1:03:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I would keep being the man who'd
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.70,1:03:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,needed it, and not the man who
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.40,1:03:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,chose her. She deserved the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.95,1:04:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,second. The first had cost her
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.68,1:04:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,two days locked in a room she
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.35,1:04:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,thought was
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.98,1:04:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,her place once again. I ran my
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.83,1:04:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,finger over her shoulder, very
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.68,1:04:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly without waking her.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.28,1:04:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be Donna. The
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.13,1:04:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,way one is named, I said. So low
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.17,1:04:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that only the fire heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.14,1:04:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She nod the way one is bought. I
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.75,1:04:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,opened the door carefully so as
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.31,1:04:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,not to wake her.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.52,1:04:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Vastian was outside, gun on his
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.33,1:04:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,thigh, eyes on the road. He
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.91,1:04:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,turned his face when he heard
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.60,1:04:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.04,1:04:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to the mansion, I said.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.53,1:04:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather all the elders and my
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.88,1:04:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,mother in the main room tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.96,1:04:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Fausto witnesses. You witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.11,1:04:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Say it's from my own hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.98,1:04:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Vastian looked inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.56,1:04:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At the rug. At her. And back at
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.97,1:04:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,me. He nodded half a degree,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.15,1:04:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,left. I stayed there until she
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.49,1:04:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,woke.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.22,1:04:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When she opened her eyes and
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.63,1:04:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at me, I knew I'd never
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.14,1:04:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,write another door again.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.82,1:04:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We stayed in the house in the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.51,1:04:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,hills the rest of Friday. I
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.09,1:04:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,slept twice more.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.36,1:04:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight what Bastion brought from
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.07,1:04:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the car. Let Ludovico tend the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.73,1:04:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,dressing on my arm one more
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.22,1:04:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.92,1:04:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He spent the afternoon on the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.46,1:05:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,phone with Fausto, arranging the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.17,1:05:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,following night.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.38,1:05:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We went back to the mansion at
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.65,1:05:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the start of Saturday evening.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.92,1:05:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the handwritten draft in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.59,1:05:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the pocket of my dress. I gave
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.25,1:05:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it back to him before going into
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.03,1:05:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.20,1:05:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,main room. Neither of us said
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.98,1:05:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,anything about it. It was agreed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.95,1:05:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,without words. The main room was
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.91,1:05:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,full.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.72,1:05:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don Vittorio, Don Emiliano, and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.76,1:05:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don Cisto seated in the high
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.61,1:05:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,chairs at the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.36,1:05:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Octavia and a sidearm chair,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.23,1:05:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,spine straight, hands crossed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.17,1:05:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,over her lap.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.42,1:05:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,With the same polite contempt of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.16,1:05:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the first day I set foot in that
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.89,1:05:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,house.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.22,1:05:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Fausto standing near the hearth,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.94,1:05:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastion leaning against the wall
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.66,1:05:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.78,1:05:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I came in without taking
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.09,1:05:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludovico's coat off my
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.29,1:05:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,shoulders. He'd covered me again
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.04,1:05:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in the car, without saying
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.78,1:05:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,anything, and I hadn't given it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.86,1:05:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.66,1:05:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I pulled my part of the contract
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.31,1:05:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from my pocket. The copy
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.55,1:05:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Donacira had brought back to me
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.15,1:05:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.46,1:05:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,old room on the first day of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.19,1:05:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,morning. I tore it in two in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.92,1:05:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,front of them. I didn't shout.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.30,1:05:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I let the pieces fall on the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.98,1:05:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,rug. I'm not leaving with any
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.72,1:05:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,fortune, I said.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.68,1:06:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor with any child under my arm,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.12,1:06:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm staying, not for the door,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.41,1:06:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.02,1:06:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Vitavia opened her mouth, closed
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.92,1:06:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it. I stared at her without
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.53,1:06:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,blinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.72,1:06:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludovico took a step forward. He
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.29,1:06:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,took the handwritten draft from
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.82,1:06:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner pocket of his jacket.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.74,1:06:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked at his mother first,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.59,1:06:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,then each of the three elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.43,1:06:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The clause was mine. He said.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.64,1:06:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The power it gave me over her
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.24,1:06:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,was mine. Now it belongs to no
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.90,1:06:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,one. He held the sheet out
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.34,1:06:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,toward the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.89,1:06:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,earth. The paper caught fire at
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.65,1:06:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the edge with an almost
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.96,1:06:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,impatient haste, as if it too
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.61,1:06:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,had waited too
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.41,1:06:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,long. He held it until the last
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.52,1:06:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,safe instant, then let go. The
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.56,1:06:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,ashes fell over the stones of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.53,1:06:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.73,1:06:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,heart. He turned to me, not to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.97,1:06:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,them. You are my equal of my
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.07,1:06:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,family. The Donah of the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.86,1:06:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Karachio Lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.39,1:06:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don Amelia no, the eldest, was
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.27,1:06:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the first to move his head. Half
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.28,1:06:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a degree. It was only half a
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.03,1:06:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.47,1:06:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was him. Don Vittorio
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.54,1:06:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,followed. Don Cisto last, with
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.75,1:06:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,an almost imperceptible delay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.65,1:07:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Latvia didn't move at all. She
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.45,1:07:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,stayed where she was. Hand still
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.37,1:07:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,crossed.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.41,1:07:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at her son the way one
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.34,1:07:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,looks at a polite stranger.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.07,1:07:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Latvia had lost. And she knew
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.94,1:07:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.61,1:07:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludovico took my hand on the way
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.35,1:07:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the room. He pulled me
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.92,1:07:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,into the corridor, away from the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.66,1:07:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.39,1:07:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And only then let out the air
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.23,1:07:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd been holding the whole
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.95,1:07:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,time. And the Sarah Valls, I
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.73,1:07:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,asked
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.69,1:07:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he raised my hand to his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.52,1:07:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Pressed his lips to my wrist.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.24,1:07:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And looked at me over my own
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.89,1:07:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.69,1:07:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow I deal with the Sarah
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.88,1:07:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Valls. Today I'm your chapter
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.99,1:07:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,six. Beneath flowers. And after
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.25,1:07:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,his weeping.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.51,1:07:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastion stood near the window of
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.90,1:07:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the breakfast room with the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.07,1:07:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,newspaper folded under his arm
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.37,1:07:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and his usual
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.93,1:07:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,face, which meant something had
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.92,1:07:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,happened. I learned that early.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.91,1:07:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When his face had no expression
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.90,1:07:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at all,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.35,1:07:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it was because he was holding
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.84,1:07:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,one. Two days had passed since
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.38,1:07:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the night of the elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.21,1:07:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The mansion breathed the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.62,1:07:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,different air. When I was still
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.45,1:07:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,learning to recognize, Dona
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.04,1:07:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiara
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.33,1:07:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,served coffee with her chin
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.81,1:08:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,higher. The corridors, which had
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.56,1:08:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,always seemed too empty.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.39,1:08:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now had people who greeted me by
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.05,1:08:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the name the family had
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.24,1:08:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,reluctantly accepted. And there
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.85,1:08:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was a
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.11,1:08:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,small but real difference in the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.18,1:08:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,way that greeting arrived. Less
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.19,1:08:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ceremony, more person.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.61,1:08:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludovico raised his eyes from
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.77,1:08:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the newspaper. Providence? He
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.93,1:08:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,asked. Boston.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.61,1:08:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastion answered. South dock.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.39,1:08:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Renolfo Saravale. Found this
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.12,1:08:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,morning with problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.19,1:08:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Problems of what order? The
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.66,1:08:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,order that doesn't ask for a
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.18,1:08:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,second visit, sir. Ludovico
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.65,1:08:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,turned his
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.19,1:08:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes back to the newspaper as if
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.84,1:08:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastion had commented on the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.29,1:08:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,weather. He turned the page with
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.95,1:08:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a calm,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.45,1:08:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I no longer found cold. I found
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.31,1:08:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it deliberate. There was a
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.87,1:08:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,difference. I picked up my cup
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.67,1:08:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with both hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.63,1:08:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,felt the warmth enter my fingers
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.97,1:08:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked nothing more. Someone
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.25,1:08:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in Providence would no longer
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.37,1:08:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,send word with dead flowers.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.59,1:08:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That was all I needed to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.97,1:08:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest I left with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.81,1:08:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nareena appeared in the doorway
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.24,1:08:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,carrying a white box wrapped in
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.67,1:08:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,green ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.43,1:09:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Cake. She announced. In that way
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.56,1:09:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,she had of turning every
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.15,1:09:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,entrance into an act.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.61,1:09:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Before anyone asks why. Bastion
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.73,1:09:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,got up and pulled a chair for
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.72,1:09:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,her. Without a word.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.57,1:09:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Without taking his eyes off the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.05,1:09:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,window. Nareena looked at the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.44,1:09:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,chair.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.27,1:09:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at him. Sat. Arranging
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.94,1:09:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the boxes ribbon on the table as
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.78,1:09:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if she'd seen nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.57,1:09:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that stone face turned
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.31,1:09:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,out kind of handsome after the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.00,1:09:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee. She said,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.31,1:09:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,loud enough for Donna Kiarra to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.99,1:09:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,hear from the kitchen. Bastion
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.62,1:09:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,coughed into a hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.71,1:09:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Change the subject by asking
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.39,1:09:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Donna Kiarra for another plate.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.25,1:09:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I filed it away somewhere inside
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.17,1:09:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.67,1:09:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The chair pulled out and the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.11,1:09:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,evirted look and the cough that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.70,1:09:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't a cough. And I didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.14,1:09:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,comment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.15,1:09:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There were stories that weren't
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.70,1:09:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,mine yet. Seven weeks later, the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.31,1:09:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,garden was covered in flowers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.41,1:09:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't wear a veil. I chose a
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.29,1:09:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,simple dress, cut at the waist,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.18,1:09:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,no train and no adornment I'd
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.94,1:09:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,need to carry.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.19,1:09:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The bouquet was of chameleas.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.59,1:09:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The same ones I'd been watering
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.08,1:09:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,since the start of that spring
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.53,1:09:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and pot scattered along the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.95,1:10:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,corridor window. A small routine
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.62,1:10:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that had become mine without my
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.25,1:10:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,noticing the exact moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.71,1:10:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nareena had helped me tie the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.34,1:10:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,white ribbon around the stems
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.97,1:10:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the night before.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.27,1:10:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Crying while she laughed at
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.58,1:10:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,herself, which was exactly her
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.04,1:10:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,way of being happy for someone.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.01,1:10:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked to the altar alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.63,1:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no one to give me
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.20,1:10:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,away. And even if there had
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.76,1:10:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,been,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.39,1:10:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have accepted. No one
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.11,1:10:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,gives away a woman who has
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.51,1:10:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,already given herself.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.69,1:10:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The morning sun came in slanted
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.48,1:10:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,between the rows of chairs. And
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.26,1:10:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the shadows of the rose stems
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.93,1:10:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,on the arch fell in long streaks
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.82,1:10:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,over the stone path. I heard my
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.65,1:10:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,own footsteps. They were the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.30,1:10:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,only ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.27,1:10:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludovico waited beneath the arch
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.78,1:10:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with his father's old watch on
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.20,1:10:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,his wrist and his arms at his
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.57,1:10:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sides.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.27,1:10:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not crossed, hiding nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.21,1:10:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,behind them. He was in a dark
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.30,1:10:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,suit. No tie. When he saw me
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.32,1:10:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,arrive, he swallowed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.41,1:10:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the movement in his
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.75,1:10:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,throat. I also saw the effort he
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.47,1:10:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,made not to let more than that
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.08,1:10:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,show.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.69,1:10:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw that the effort wasn't
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.59,1:10:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,enough. Nareena cried,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.17,1:10:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,prettyly, seated in the front
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.04,1:10:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,row, with Donna Kiarra's hand
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.91,1:11:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,over hers. Donna Kiarra cried in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.98,1:11:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,an ugly
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.43,1:11:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,way, an embroidered handkerchief
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.38,1:11:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,pressed to her nose. Her
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.85,1:11:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,shoulders shaking in generous
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.62,1:11:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.81,1:11:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastion was in a tie as few
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.57,1:11:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,times as I'd ever seen him. A
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.47,1:11:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,dark gray tie, meticulously
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.23,1:11:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,nodded.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.19,1:11:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The only sign that that morning
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.60,1:11:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,was different from all the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.79,1:11:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,others. Nareena turned to the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.11,1:11:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,nearest
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.43,1:11:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,person and said it loud enough
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.21,1:11:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach the altar. If he
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.69,1:11:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,blinked twice in a row, she
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.29,1:11:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,said,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.03,1:11:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a smile. Bastion blinked
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.01,1:11:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,twice in a row, without turning
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.13,1:11:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,his face. I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.75,1:11:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Atavia was in the front row on
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.47,1:11:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the right side, in a dark blue
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.19,1:11:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,wool dress, and the bearing of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.91,1:11:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who came because she
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.60,1:11:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,needed to be seen. She was
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.17,1:11:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,invited. She accepted out of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.87,1:11:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.13,1:11:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't look at her once, and
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.82,1:11:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when the priest began to speak,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.56,1:11:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized I also wouldn't need
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.31,1:11:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to. The priest said short
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.11,1:11:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,things. Ludovico said his vow so
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.41,1:11:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,low that the chameleas barely
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.50,1:11:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,heard it,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.31,1:11:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but I heard it. He said he'd
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.99,1:11:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,learned, too late, that love
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.67,1:11:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't guaranteed with a clause,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.91,1:12:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that he'd spend the rest of his
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.42,1:12:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,life without writing any exit
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.83,1:12:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,door for me. That if one day I
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.29,1:12:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to leave, it would have
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.77,1:12:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to be me walking, because he'd
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.25,1:12:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no longer build the exit with
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.68,1:12:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,his own hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.77,1:12:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I said my vow looking at him. I
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.77,1:12:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,chose to stay. I'll keep
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.32,1:12:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,choosing every day. He kissed me
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.39,1:12:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.65,1:12:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,no contract between us. No door.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.56,1:12:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With the morning sun on my back
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.40,1:12:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the smell of Camilla in the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.19,1:12:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,air,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.83,1:12:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and his hands on both sides of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.41,1:12:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,my face, as if I were the only
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.99,1:12:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,stable thing in a world he'd
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.47,1:12:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,spent his whole life trying to
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.38,1:12:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,control. Winter came heavy in
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.23,1:12:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Providence. Enrico was born on a
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.27,1:12:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,late January dawn, with snow
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.20,1:12:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,falling outside the window and
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.27,1:12:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,thick quiet pieces. No wind, as
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.41,1:12:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,if time
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.89,1:12:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,had decided to be gentle at that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.07,1:12:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,hour. Labor was long. Ludovico
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.11,1:12:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't leave the room once. He
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.15,1:12:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,held my hand through every
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.70,1:12:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,contraction. His forehead
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.20,1:12:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,pressed to mine. murmuring
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.75,1:12:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,things in
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.29,1:12:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Italian that I'd begun to
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.39,1:12:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,understand because of how much
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.72,1:12:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he murmured near me in hours
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.96,1:12:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,without witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.27,1:12:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside, Narina waited with
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.98,1:12:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Donna Kiarra, and an absurd
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.70,1:13:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,basket with enough sandwiches to
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.73,1:13:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,feed a whole battalion, because
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.56,1:13:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that was her way of enduring the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.45,1:13:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,weight. Bastion stood in the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.10,1:13:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,corridor
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.57,1:13:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with the gun hidden under his
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.59,1:13:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,jacket, protecting something
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.55,1:13:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that had no enemy that dawn.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.50,1:13:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico came
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.27,1:13:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world with a strong
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.85,1:13:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,cry. The size the family had
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.43,1:13:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,waited for over three
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.61,1:13:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,generations.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.49,1:13:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The obstetrician placed him on
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.54,1:13:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,my chest first. He stopped
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.32,1:13:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,crying almost at once,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.15,1:13:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as if he recognized the place. I
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.20,1:13:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,stayed looking at him. That tiny
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.25,1:13:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,piece of a person with wet
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.91,1:13:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,black lashes and hands closed
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.64,1:13:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,into small fists, and I found no
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.54,1:13:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,word sufficient for what I felt.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.89,1:13:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't try. Ludovico took him
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.81,1:13:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,afterward. He held his son in
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.61,1:13:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,his arms with both hands open.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.47,1:13:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The small body lost in his large
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.51,1:13:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,arms, and stayed motionless for
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.49,1:13:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a few seconds just looking.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.69,1:13:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was when he wept. He
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.60,1:13:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't hide it. He didn't turn
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.57,1:13:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,his face. He didn't run his hand
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.67,1:13:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,over his eyes as if wiping away
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.52,1:13:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,something else. He wept looking
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.38,1:14:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at his son. His chin trembling
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.17,1:14:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tears running down the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.79,1:14:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,line of his jaw without him
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.24,1:14:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,making any gesture to stop them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.17,1:14:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,With a stillness that was only
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.16,1:14:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,his, and that I'd never seen in
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.21,1:14:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,any of the faces he used in the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.27,1:14:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,nose. He said low to me when he
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.67,1:14:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,found his voice. Poor thing. I
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.99,1:14:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,answered. He laughed in the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.09,1:14:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,middle
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.55,1:14:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the weeping. He leaned his
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.11,1:14:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,forehead against mine. That
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.56,1:14:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,gesture that had become our
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.02,1:14:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,private language.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.47,1:14:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he leaned his forehead
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.88,1:14:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,against in Riko's too, closing
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.44,1:14:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the triangle among the three of
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.05,1:14:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,us.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.49,1:14:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And we stayed like that for a
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.24,1:14:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,time I couldn't measure. In
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.86,1:14:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Riko, he said, you were right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.13,1:14:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd suggested the name weeks
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.55,1:14:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,before. On an ordinary night
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.97,1:14:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,while we waited for the snow to
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.55,1:14:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,stop outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.21,1:14:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And Riko, in honor of his
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.96,1:14:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,brother, the one who died at 19
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.13,1:14:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in a story he told me only once.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.77,1:14:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Slowly, without a dormant.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.34,1:14:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Lutaviko had looked at me for a
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.20,1:14:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,long time when I said it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.97,1:14:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Without saying yes or no, as if
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.50,1:14:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,he needed to carry the name a
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.93,1:14:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,little before giving his answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.05,1:14:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Only now, with his son and his
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.96,1:15:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,arms and the weeping he didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.88,1:15:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,hide, was he saying yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.93,1:15:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Six months after the birth, the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.57,1:15:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,morning in the suite was one of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.21,1:15:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the calmest the mansion had ever
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.91,1:15:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.17,1:15:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And Riko slept in the crib in
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.87,1:15:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the room next door. And the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.45,1:15:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,monitor beside my side of the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.16,1:15:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,bed,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.91,1:15:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,purred with his breathing. That
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.49,1:15:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,sound that had become the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.76,1:15:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,soundtrack of my small hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.73,1:15:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The June light came through the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.36,1:15:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,cracks and the shutters and wide
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.05,1:15:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,warm bands.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.05,1:15:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lutaviko came in carrying a tray
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.21,1:15:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with two cups, bear foot, no
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.09,1:15:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,jacket, in the previous day's
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.05,1:15:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,shirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.87,1:15:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat on the edge of the bed
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.64,1:15:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and handed me mine. Two sugar
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.41,1:15:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,cubes, a drop of milk.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.75,1:15:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I laughed softly. The way one
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.41,1:15:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,laughs at an old joke that keeps
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.24,1:15:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,working out of love for what it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.01,1:15:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,means.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.77,1:15:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember? I asked. That I
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.93,1:15:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,told you once months ago, my
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.82,1:15:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,mother's dream. He already knew
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.91,1:15:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which question it was. I saw it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.96,1:15:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in the way he held his own cup.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.02,1:15:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Unhurried. He let me finish
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.81,1:15:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.85,1:15:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A library I continued. In
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.38,1:15:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,federal hill, free books for the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.33,1:15:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,neighborhood children.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.21,1:16:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She never had money to put a
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.41,1:16:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,book in my hand that wasn't
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.56,1:16:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,borrowed from the school or from
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.93,1:16:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,someone
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.23,1:16:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who owed a favor. I bought the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.95,1:16:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,building three months ago. He
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.62,1:16:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,answered, looking at his cup.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.81,1:16:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The work began last Monday. I
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.20,1:16:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't tell you because I wanted
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.73,1:16:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it to be a surprise when the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.07,1:16:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,sign went up. It was going up
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.84,1:16:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,next week. I stayed quiet. The
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.67,1:16:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,band of sun crossed the sheet
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.44,1:16:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.43,1:16:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The sign. I asked softly. What's
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.78,1:16:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it going to say? Marcecano
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.69,1:16:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Community Library. Your mother's
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.05,1:16:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,maiden name.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.27,1:16:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You told me one dinner night and
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.00,1:16:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,passing. The way one tells
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.41,1:16:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,something without expecting
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.87,1:16:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.85,1:16:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept it. I set the cup on the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.45,1:16:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,nightstand before I could spill
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.05,1:16:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the coffee over the sheet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.85,1:16:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I leaned my forehead against
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.29,1:16:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,his. We stayed like that a good
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.88,1:16:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,while,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.71,1:16:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,without either of us finding a
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.38,1:16:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,word worth more than the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.71,1:16:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,silence. In Rico woke shortly
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.32,1:16:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,after.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.19,1:16:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I nursed him. Changed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.67,1:16:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Handed him to Ludovico so he
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.26,1:16:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could make the baby laugh with
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.96,1:16:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that stone
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.53,1:16:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,face that no longer fooled
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.82,1:16:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone. At the end of the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.06,1:16:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,morning we went down to the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.40,1:16:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,winter garden.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.43,1:16:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I took in Rico in my arm so he
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.06,1:17:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,could see the chameleas. The
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.59,1:17:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,same ones that had become my
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.11,1:17:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,bouquet.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.85,1:17:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And that I still watered now
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.41,1:17:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with him on my hip, showing him
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.13,1:17:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the flowers as if he knew what
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.79,1:17:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.41,1:17:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he did. Ludovico sat
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.94,1:17:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,beside me on the stone bench
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.59,1:17:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with the coffee he'd brought
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.23,1:17:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,down from upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.11,1:17:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Still warm. The June sun came
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.87,1:17:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,through the glass panes at a low
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.82,1:17:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,angle, warming the stone without
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.76,1:17:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,burning.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.81,1:17:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the morning? He
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.47,1:17:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,said in a low tone. When I
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.86,1:17:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,received an envelope and put it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.52,1:17:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the drawer,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.27,1:17:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered at once. The
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.75,1:17:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,morning after the night
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.11,1:17:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everything had shifted sides. On
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.00,1:17:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the other side
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.83,1:17:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of months, and of all that came
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.65,1:17:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,after. The old envelope sealed
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.42,1:17:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with the crest of the lion with
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.24,1:17:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the broken
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.83,1:17:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,crown. He'd put it away unopened
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.84,1:17:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of me and hugged me too
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.86,1:17:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,tight for an ordinary Saturday
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.75,1:17:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.77,1:17:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember. I answered. You
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.51,1:17:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,hugged me too tight for it to be
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.57,1:17:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing. He ran his hand slowly
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.57,1:17:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,over
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.83,1:17:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Rico's hair, who slept against
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.60,1:17:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,my shoulder with his mouth
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.14,1:17:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,slightly open. It really was
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.80,1:17:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.93,1:18:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the beginning. I stayed
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.62,1:18:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at him. The winter
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.19,1:18:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,garden was in a good silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.95,1:18:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.43,1:18:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that asks for no filling. In
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.25,1:18:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Rico breathe deep against my
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.06,1:18:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,neck. Ludovico's hand was open
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.01,1:18:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,over mine
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.59,1:18:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two bodies in the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.59,1:18:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,middle of the stone bench,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.38,1:18:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,without grip, without weight.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.37,1:18:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Just there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.57,1:18:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought of the islanda who'd
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.98,1:18:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,waited at the altar of the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.20,1:18:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,church and providence in a white
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.70,1:18:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,dress
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.93,1:18:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with a bell-tolling 12 times to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.88,1:18:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,say what the whole city already
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.83,1:18:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,knew. She was another person.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.31,1:18:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She was me, but she was another
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.26,1:18:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,person. The one who didn't yet
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.16,1:18:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,know that humiliation can be the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.17,1:18:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,first
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.49,1:18:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,step of a path worth walking.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.26,1:18:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ludovico raised my hand and
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.92,1:18:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,kissed my wrist. Slowly, without
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.87,1:18:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,announcement.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.41,1:18:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In Rico let out a small sigh on
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.30,1:18:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,my shoulder. Outside, the white
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.19,1:18:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,chameleas swayed lightly with
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.96,1:18:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the wind
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.45,1:18:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,coming through the gap in the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.27,1:18:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,garden door. The butt wife of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.10,1:18:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Providence had a price. No one,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.13,1:18:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not even he knew it was this, to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.07,1:18:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,stay.